#!/usr/bin/perl
# prints the number needed to get a specific letter name in an Indesign page
# maximum: 99999 = eqxc
$a = "a";
for (1 .. 99999) {
  $hash{$a++} = $_;
}

print $hash{lc($ARGV[0])} , "\n";

__END__

Really, computers are too fast these days. I spent more time trying to figure
out the right formula to calculate this properly than it would ever save to
actually do so, given that the computer runs this program in .07 seconds.
